 \\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Task T-010@20260416T043834Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"T-010@20260416T043834Z\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"2026-04-16T10:43:13.047993+00:00\\\\\\\"}\\\\n {\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"codex\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\": 711.779, \\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Task T-011@20260416T043834Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"T-011@20260416T043834Z\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"2026-04-16T10:55:18.190986+00:00\\\\\\\"}\\\\n+{\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\": 1335.982, \\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Task T-021@20260416T043834Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"T-021@20260416T043834Z\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"2026-04-16T11:17:57.488895+00:00\\\\\\\"}\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/run-log.md b/sdp/run-log.md\\\\nindex c3145a0..16e9d89 100644\\\\n--- a/sdp/run-log.md\\\\n+++ b/sdp/run-log.md\\\\n@@ -40,3 +40,4 @@\\\\n | run-t-009@20260416t043834z-1776334109 | T-009@20260416T043834Z | claude | gemini | PASS | 1349.6s | — |\\\\n | run-t-010@20260416t043834z-1776335471 | T-010@20260416T043834Z | claude | codex | PASS WITH NOTES | 709.3s | — |\\\\n | run-t-011@20260416t043834z-1776336193 | T-011@20260416T043834Z | codex | claude | PASS | 711.8s | — |\\\\n+| run-t-021@20260416t043834z-1776336919 | T-021@20260416T043834Z | claude | codex | PASS WITH NOTES | 1336.0s | — |\\\\ndiff --git a/specs/t-022@20260416t043834z-spec.md b/specs/t-022@20260416t043834z-spec.md\\\\nnew file mode 100644\\\\nindex 0000000..5d25cc3\\\\n--- /dev/null\\\\n+++ b/specs/t-022@20260416t043834z-spec.md\\\\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\\\\n+# Specification: T-022@20260416T043834Z\\\\n+\\\\n+## Problem Statement\\\\n+CypherClaw's SenseWeave requires abstractions to manage real-time environmental input (live buffers) and long-term retention of notable audio events (sample banks). We need a stable representation of the current audio buffer and a mechanism to persistently archive valuable clips with associated metadata.\\\\n+\\\\n+## Technical Approach\\\\n+1. Create a new module `my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`.\\\\n+2. Define a `LiveBuffer` class that exposes `source_name`, `capture_path`, `freshness`, `rms`, `spectral_profile`, and `transform_history`. Provide a method to refresh this state from new sensory data.\\\\n+3. Define a `SampleBankStorage` (or `SampleArchive`) class representing the \\\\\\\"sample bank\\\\\\\" abstraction. It will handle copying/moving selected clips to an archive directory and storing associated metadata (e.g., as JSON files side-by-side with the audio).\\\\n+4. Create comprehensive tests in `tests/test_live_buffer.py` to ensure `LiveBuffer` state updates correctly upon refresh, and that `SampleBankStorage` accurately selects archive paths and persists metadata.\\\\n+\\\\n+## Edge Cases\\\\n+- Missing source files during retention (should gracefully fail or return `None`).\\\\n+- Empty spectral profiles or missing RMS values on refresh (should default to zeros or retain previous valid values based on the semantics).\\\\n+- Metadata persistence formatting and safety.\\\\n+\\\\n+## Acceptance Criteria\\\\n+- stable buffers expose source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, and transform history\\\\n+  - VERIFY: `grep -q \\\\\\\"class LiveBuffer\\\\\\\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`\\\\n+- sample banks can retain selected clips on archive storage with metadata\\\\n+  - VERIFY: `grep -q \\\\\\\"def retain_clip\\\\\\\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/live_buffer.py`\\\\n+- tests verify buffer refresh and archive path selection\\\\n+  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_live_buffer.py -x`\\\\ndiff --git a/tests/test_live_buffer.py b/tests/test_live_buffer.py\\\\nnew file mode 100644\\\\nindex 0000000..3bdd45f\\\\n--- /dev/null\\\\n+++ b/tests/test_live_buffer.py\\\\n@@ -0,0 +1,85 @@\\\\n+import json\\\\n+import os\\\\n+import sys\\\\n+import time\\\\n+from pathlib import Path\\\\n+\\\\n+import pytest\\\\n+\\\\n+sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \\\\\\\"..\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"my-claw\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"tools\\\\\\\"))\\\\n+sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \\\\\\\"..\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"my-claw\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"tools\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"senseweave\\\\\\\"))\\\\n+\\\\n+from senseweave.live_buffer import LiveBuffer, SampleBankArchive\\\\n+\\\\n+def test_live_buffer_refresh():\\\\n+    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Verify buffer refresh exposes source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, and transform history.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    buffer = LiveBuffer(source_name=\\\\\\\"room_mic\\\\\\\", capture_path=\\\\\\\"/tmp/room_mic.wav\\\\\\\")\\\\n+    \\\\n+    assert buffer.source_name == \\\\\\\"room_mic\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    assert buffer.capture_path == \\\\\\\"/tmp/room_mic.wav\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    assert buffer.freshness == 0.0\\\\n+    assert buffer.rms == 0.0\\\\n+    assert buffer.spectral_profile == {}\\\\n+    assert buffer.transform_history == ()\\\\n+    \\\\n+    # Refresh\\\\n+    buffer.refresh(\\\\n+        freshness=12.5,\\\\n+        rms=0.45,\\\\n+        spectral_profile={\\\\\\\"centroid\\\\\\\": 1200.0, \\\\\\\"rolloff\\\\\\\": 3400.0},\\\\n+        transform_history=(\\\\\\\"stretch\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pitch_window\\\\\\\")\\\\n+    )\\\\n+    \\\\n+    assert buffer.freshness == 12.5\\\\n+    assert buffer.rms == 0.45\\\\n+    assert buffer.spectral_profile == {\\\\\\\"centroid\\\\\\\": 1200.0, \\\\\\\"rolloff\\\\\\\": 3400.0}\\\\n+    assert buffer.transform_history == (\\\\\\\"stretch\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pitch_window\\\\\\\")\\\\n+\\\\n+def test_sample_bank_archive_path_selection(tmp_path):\\\\n+    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Verify sample banks can retain selected clips on archive storage with metadata.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    archive_dir = tmp_path / \\\\\\\"sample_archive\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    archive = SampleBankArchive(archive_dir=archive_dir)\\\\n+    \\\\n+    # Create a dummy source file\\\\n+    source_file = tmp_path / \\\\\\\"source.wav\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    source_file.write_bytes(b\\\\\\\"dummy wav content\\\\\\\")\\\\n+    \\\\n+    metadata = {\\\\n+        \\\\\\\"source_name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"contact_mic\\\\\\\",\\\\n+        \\\\\\\"rms\\\\\\\": 0.8,\\\\n+        \\\\\\\"spectral_profile\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\"centroid\\\\\\\": 500.0},\\\\n+        \\\\\\\"tags\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"impulse\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"body\\\\\\\"]\\\\n+    }\\\\n+    \\\\n+    archived_path = archive.retain_clip(\\\\n+        source_path=source_file,\\\\n+        source_name=\\\\\\\"contact_mic\\\\\\\",\\\\n+        metadata=metadata\\\\n+    )\\\\n+    \\\\n+    assert archived_path is not None\\\\n+    assert archived_path.exists()\\\\n+    assert archived_path.parent == archive_dir / \\\\\\\"contact_mic\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    assert archived_path.suffix == \\\\\\\".wav\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    \\\\n+    # Verify metadata is stored\\\\n+    meta_path = archived_path.with_suffix(\\\\\\\".json\\\\\\\")\\\\n+    assert meta_path.exists()\\\\n+    \\\\n+    saved_meta = json.loads(meta_path.read_text())\\\\n+    assert saved_meta[\\\\\\\"source_name\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\"contact_mic\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    assert saved_meta[\\\\\\\"rms\\\\\\\"] == 0.8\\\\n+    assert saved_meta[\\\\\\\"tags\\\\\\\"] == [\\\\\\\"impulse\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"body\\\\\\\"]\\\\n+    assert \\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\" in saved_meta\\\\n+\\\\n+def test_sample_bank_archive_missing_file(tmp_path):\\\\n+    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Verify archive fails gracefully when source file is missing.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n+    archive = SampleBankArchive(archive_dir=tmp_path / \\\\\\\"archive\\\\\\\")\\\\n+    \\\\n+    archived_path = archive.retain_clip(\\\\n+        source_path=tmp_path / \\\\\\\"nonexistent.wav\\\\\\\",\\\\n+        source_name=\\\\\\\"room_mic\\\\\\\",\\\\n+        metadata={}\\\\n+    )\\\\n+    \\\\n+    assert archived_path is None\\\"}\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:++4. **Logged escalations** — hardening items (`bootstrap_identity`) are unrelated to this task; previous lead's out-of-scope changes documented\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:+- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (self-critique and revision passes for music composition) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:+- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:+- [ ] [blocking] Candidate hardening checks remain unresolved for this task: bootstrap-first-run identity persistence (`bootstrap_identity` + `FirstBootAnnouncer`, both standalone and federated paths) is not implemented here. This is recorded in `ESCALATIONS.md` as out-of-scope.\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:+- If this task is expected to absorb startup hardening from recurring checks, wire `bootstrap_identity` into startup initialization and add the requested cross-mode startup persistence regression test.\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-024_20260416T043834Z_1776345043.log:++- *