sdp/verification/t-016@20260515t214233z-verify.md:28:2. Payload and route metadata record `workflow_id: shutdown_audit`, `mutating_actions: []`, executed tools, and all three state fields — confirmed.
sdp/verification/t-016@20260515t214233z-verify.md:44:The workflow is strictly read-only: `mutating_actions: []` is enforced at both the payload and route layer. The SSH remote command only reads `/opt/pal/config/shutdown.conf`, checks override file presence, reads crontab, captures local time, and tails shutdown logs — no writes, no cron edits, no override flag mutations. No PAL router is invoked. No new dependencies or provider secrets are introduced. No action IDs are exposed. The spec's explicit prohibition list (touching `override.flag`, editing cron, calling the PAL router, shutting down the host) is satisfied.
